From: meta-nxp-mr <peter@navq.local>
Date: Thu, 26 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] meson: disable DRI3 explicit sync to match noble libxcb 1.15

The Yocto sysroot ships libxcb/xcb-proto 1.17, so Mesa enables its DRI3 1.4
explicit-sync WSI path and references xcb_present_pixmap_synced and
xcb_dri3_import_syncobj_checked. This image runs on an Ubuntu/noble rootfs whose
runtime libxcb is 1.15 and does NOT export those symbols, so the resulting
libvulkan_panfrost.so (PanVK) fails the loader's undefined-symbol check and is
ignored -> vkCreateInstance reports "Found no drivers".

Force with_dri3_explicit_sync off so the symbols are compiled out; Mesa falls back
to the non-explicit-sync DRI3/Present path.

Upstream-Status: Inappropriate [BSP runtime-ABI workaround for Ubuntu-rootfs trick]
---
--- a/meson.build	2026-06-26 10:28:46.638851464 +0200
+++ b/meson.build	2026-06-26 10:28:46.654851574 +0200
@@ -2175,7 +2175,12 @@
   if with_dri_platform == 'drm'
     dep_xcb_dri3 = dependency('xcb-dri3', version : dep_xcb_dri3_version)
     dep_xcb_present = dependency('xcb-present', version : dep_xcb_present_version)
-    if (dep_xcb_dri3.version().version_compare('>= 1.17') and
+    # meta-nxp-mr: the runtime libxcb is the Ubuntu/noble rootfs's 1.15, which
+    # lacks xcb_present_pixmap_synced / xcb_dri3_import_syncobj (DRI3 1.4 explicit
+    # sync, new in libxcb/xcb-proto 1.17). Building against the Yocto sysroot's
+    # libxcb 1.17 would make the Mesa .so reference those symbols and fail to load
+    # on the board ("Found no drivers"). Force-disable so they are compiled out.
+    if (false and dep_xcb_dri3.version().version_compare('>= 1.17') and
         dep_xcb_present.version().version_compare('>= 1.17'))
       with_dri3_explicit_sync = true
     endif
